{"word":"χελιχελώνη","slug":"χελιχελώνη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n113744\" key=\"xelixelw/nh\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">χελιχελώνη</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen>, a girls' game, in which a ring was formed round a player called <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">χελώνη,</foreign> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0542.tlg001:9:125\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Poll.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.125</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4083.tlg001:1914:54\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Eust.\">Eust.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1914.54</biblScope></bibl>. The <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">χελι-</foreign> seems to be merely an iteration of the first syll. in <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">χελώνη;</foreign> cf. <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Carm.Pop.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">21</biblScope> </bibl> (written <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">χέλει χ.</foreign> Eust.l.c.).</entryFree>"}]}